data.title: About: F. D. Reeve
data.meta_description: Franklin D'Olier Reeve (September 18, 1928 – June 28, 2013) was an American academic, writer, poet, Russian translator, and editor. He was also the father of "Superman" actor Christopher Reeve. He was the grandson of the first American Legion national commander, Franklin D'Olier.
data.text:
dbo:abstract

إف. د. ريف (بالإنجليزية: F. D. Reeve)‏ هو مترجم وشاعر أمريكي، ولد في 18 سبتمبر 1928 في فيلادلفيا في الولايات المتحدة، وتوفي في 28 يونيو 2013 في لبنان في الولايات المتحدة بسبب السكري. (ar)

Franklin D'Olier Reeve (September 18, 1928 – June 28, 2013) was an American academic, writer, poet, Russian translator, and editor. He was also the father of "Superman" actor Christopher Reeve. He was the grandson of the first American Legion national commander, Franklin D'Olier. (en)
